covered: Valid Request scenarios are well covered: default retrieval and parameterized requests (offset/limit, audit, balance flags).
Empty Response handling is covered: no accounts, offset beyond data, and edge cases with missing data (TC08, TC09, TC43).
Pagination coverage is thorough: offset/limit variations, boundary conditions, large datasets, performance considerations, and concurrency (TC02, TC21, TC19, TC20, TC31, TC50).

Query Parameters handling is comprehensive: boolean flags (accountWithBalance, accountWithBalanceAndCBA), audit values, invalid inputs, and extra parameters ignored (TC03, TC04, TC05, TC06, TC07, TC10-TC14, TC25, TC38-TC39, TC14, TC29).
Authorization handling is addressed: missing credentials and invalid token scenarios (TC15, TC16).
Error handling and security scenarios are covered: invalid inputs (400), method not allowed (405), security tests (SQLi/XSS) (TC40, TC23, TC24), and related edge cases (TC41).
Integration and resilience scenarios are tested: service unavailability, dependency failures, and recovery (TC17, TC32, TC33, TC36, TC37).
Performance and scalability tests are included: large data volume (TC19) and degraded performance under load (TC31).
State variation and recovery are represented: partially populated database, recovery from transient errors (TC30, TC36, TC37).
Accessibility and audit considerations are covered: JSON structure validity, screen-reader compatibility, and audit-log consistency (TC34, TC33, TC35).
gaps: Rate limiting (throttling) tests under burst traffic are not covered.
Caching behavior tests (ETag/Cache-Control) and related cache validation (e.g., 304) are not covered.
403 Forbidden scenarios (authenticated but lacking permissions) are not explicitly tested.
500 Internal Server Error scenarios (beyond 503 Service Unavailable) are not covered.
Observability aspects (correlation IDs, logging/metrics) are not tested.
Tests for parameter parsing resilience on duplicate or conflicting query keys are not explicit.
recommendations: Add rate-limiting/throttling tests to verify behavior under burst traffic and ensure proper error handling.
Add caching tests to validate caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) and behavior on unchanged data (304 Not Modified).
Introduce 403 Forbidden scenarios to cover authenticated users without sufficient permissions.
Add 500 Internal Server Error test cases to cover unexpected server failures.
Include observability tests for correlation IDs and server-side logs to improve traceability.
Add tests for handling of duplicate/conflicting query parameters to strengthen parameter parsing resilience.
